application_process:
To apply for the Golden Passport for seniors 65 years of age or older, applicant must complete the Golden Passport EASY Card Application and provide a valid state-issued Florida DriverGs License or Florida ID showing a Miami-Dade County physical address.

To apply for the Golden Passport Social Security beneficiaries under 65 years of age, you must submit a current printout from the Social Security Services Administration verifying eligibility. Proof of continued eligibility must be provided annually. Applicant must also bring their physical Social Security Card and a valid state-issued Florida DriverGs License or Florida ID showing a Miami-Dade County physical address.

You can also register at 3-1-1 Centers

You can also register at 3-1-1 Centers

application_process:
Must call the Medical Center number to speak with a social worker and setup an appointment day and time, and must meet the following requirements:

* Proof of legal residency in the United States, i.e.  citizenship, residence or legal notification  from immigration and constancy that specify applicant continuously have resided in the State of Florida for at least one year (12 months).
* Social Security card.
* Copies of the last three income taxes (yours, head of family or individual responsible for your financial support).
* Clinical history with cancer diagnosis and pathology.
* Referral letter from attending physician to Liga Contra el C+ncer.
* If you have medical insurance that does not cover cancer treatment bring a letter from the insurance company stating so.
* Proof of household monthly income, including pay stubs, disability, alimony, child support, social security, retirement and food stamps.
* Rent or mortgage statements, as well as, electricity, gas and telephone bills.
* If you live with relative(s) or friend(s), bring notarized letter from the head of the household stating that you are aggregated member to their household, as well as copies of the three last income taxes of the head of the family.
* Copy of last three months of all bank statements.
* Present a copy of your Medicaid application. Should you have not applied yet, you have to do it immediately. If you are ineligible, please bring copy of their notification.
name: Volunteer Opportunities

application_process:
* Bring each family member who is applying to receive WIC services.

* Bring proof of all income for everyone in the household (before taxes and deductions are taken out).

* Bring one proof of where you live 

* Bring one proof of identification for you and one proof of identification for any infant or child applying for WIC, such as a birth certificate, driver's license, crib card, military ID, photo ID, Social Security Card, or hospital record.

* Bring the Social Security Number for each person applying for WIC, if available.

* Bring the immunization (shot) record for each child.

* For EACH woman, infant, and child applying for WIC, you will need: 
- A recent height and weight measurement (no older than 60 days)
- Hemoglobin or hematocrit blood test results (not required for infants under 9 months).
- Ask your doctor or health clinic to fill out this health information on a WIC Medical Referral Form or, the WIC office will help you get this health information.

* Bring one proof of identification for you and one proof of identification for any infant or child applying for WIC, such as a birth certificate, driver's license, crib card, military ID, photo ID, Social Security Card, or hospital record.

* Bring the Social Security Number for each person applying for WIC, if available.

* Bring the immunization (shot) record for each child.

* For EACH woman, infant, and child applying for WIC, you will need: 
- A recent height and weight measurement (no older than 60 days)
- Hemoglobin or hematocrit blood test results (not required for infants under 9 months).
- Ask your doctor or health clinic to fill out this health information on a WIC Medical Referral Form or, the WIC office will help you get this health information.

application_process:
A Parent/Guardian for the student must write to The On It Foundation requesting a free computer. Information in the letter must provide the following: 

Student Name, Age, Grade, School Name, School Address and School Phone Information

Parent/Guardian Name, Address, Phone Number. *Please note GThe Letter of RequestG for a free computer must be signed by the Parent/Guardian.

Require proof from the school on its letterhead that the student qualifies for free or reduced school lunch. 

Mail Letter of Request and statement from the school 

May e-mail the Letter of Request (as long as the original signature is included in the letter); However, The On It Foundation requires the original statement from the school regarding the student's confirmation that he/she is on the free or reduced school lunch program. 

Please send an e-mail to Info@TheOnItFoundation.org
name: Computer Donation Programs

application_process:
Provide a valid Florida DriverGs License or Florida ID card displaying current Monroe County address.  
If these forms of identification are not available, or if the address is not current or local, an applicant may provide a valid, government-issued photo ID card with one of the following:

* Monroe County Property Tax Receipt or Business License
* Pay stub, IRS return or printed bank checks showing applicantGs name and local address
* A current residential lease of at least 6 months
* Monroe County School or Employer ID
* Current Monroe County Utility Bills
* Monroe County VoterGs Registration Card
* Current Monroe County Vehicle or Vessel Registration

application_process:
To apply for the Patriot Passport eligible veterans must complete the Patriot Passport EASY Card Application found online.

Disabled veterans need to provide:

DD214 form showing proof of an honorable discharge.
A VA disability letter showing percentage of disability.
A Valid state-issued Florida DriverGs License or Florida ID showing a Miami-Dade County physical address.
Proof of Income * Consecutive pay stubs, weekly (4-pay stubs), bi-weekly (2-pay stubs) if paid monthly (1-pay stub) or current income tax return or IRS Tax Return Transcript Income Tax W2 wages statement.

Other veterans need to provide: 

Proof of Income * Consecutive pay stubs, weekly (4-pay stubs), bi-weekly (2-pay stubs) if paid monthly (1-pay stub) or current income tax return or IRS Tax Return Transcript.
Income Tax W2 wages statement.
Current valid Florida ID or driver's license with a Miami-Dade County physical address.
DD214 form as proof of an honorable discharge.
Proof of income, Social Security number and a valid Florida ID or Florida driver's license with a Miami-Dade County physical address must be provided annually to receive continued benefits.
name: Free Transit Passes

application_process:
Must fill out LIHEAP Application and submit with:

* Original copy of energy bill.
* Copy of Social Security cards for all household members.
* Copy of Applicants' ID (Driver's License, FL ID, or Voter Registration Card).
* Copy of proof of income for every member of the household for the prior month.

Proof of Income options: Consecutive Pay stubs- weekly: 4 pay stubs, bi-weekly: 2 pay stubs, if paid once a month then 1 pay stub; letter from employer on company letterhead stating income from prior month or current income tax return

Income Award Letter(s):
* SSA, SSI, VA, Pension, Welfare/TANF
* Child Support/Alimony
* Self Employed Income or Financial Support from Friends or Family

* Income Self Declaration Form provided at Service Centers.

Proof of Assistance:
* Food Stamps
* Weatherization Assistance Program
* Community Services Block Grant Program

**Service Centers WILL NOT make copies of required documents.**
name: Electric Service Payment Assistance

* Copy of Social Security cards for all household members.
* Copy of Applicants' ID (Driver's License, FL ID, or Voter Registration Card).
* Copy of proof of income for every member of the household for the prior month.

Proof of Income options: Consecutive Pay stubs- weekly: 4 pay stubs, bi-weekly: 2 pay stubs, if paid once a month then 1 pay stub; letter from employer on company letterhead stating income from prior month or current income tax return

Income Award Letter(s):
* SSA, SSI, VA, Pension, Welfare/TANF
* Child Support/Alimony
* Self Employed Income or Financial Support from Friends or Family

* Income Self Declaration Form provided at Service Centers.

Proof of Assistance:
* Food Stamps
* Weatherization Assistance Program
* Community Services Block Grant Program

**Service Centers WILL NOT make copies of required documents.**
name: Electric Service Payment Assistance

application_process:
* Bring each family member who is applying to receive WIC services.

* Bring proof of all income for everyone in the household (before taxes and deductions are taken out).

* Bring one proof of where you live 

* Bring one proof of identification for you and one proof of identification for any infant or child applying for WIC, such as a birth certificate, driver's license, crib card, military ID, photo ID, Social Security Card, or hospital record.

* Bring the Social Security Number for each person applying for WIC, if available.

* Bring the immunization (shot) record for each child.

* For EACH woman, infant, and child applying for WIC, you will need: 
- A recent height and weight measurement (no older than 60 days)
- Hemoglobin or hematocrit blood test results (not required for infants under 9 months).
- Ask your doctor or health clinic to fill out this health information on a WIC Medical Referral Form or, the WIC office will help you get this health information.

application_process:
A new application requires that a picture of the patron be taken at Transit Service Center for placement on the newly issued EASY Card.

A Valid state-issued Florida DriverGs License or Florida ID showing a Miami-Dade County physical address.

Physical copy of Social Security Card.

Annual income cannot exceed $17,801. 

Proof of Income: Current Tax Return, Current W-2, 2 Paycheck stubs for the last 30 days.

Application must be filled out completely and signed by applicant in order to be processed by Golden Passport staff. 

Transit Mobility EASY Card is valid for one year and requires annual renewal. 

Applicants under the age of 18 must meet the above requirements and must also be accompanied by a parent or legal guardian.
name: Full Fare Transit Passes

application_process:
Appointment Required, call for more information.


Bring the following documents: 
*Proof of identification (photo ID)
*Social Security cards for you, your spouse and dependents 
*An Individual Taxpayer Identification Number (ITIN) assignment letter may be substituted    for you, your spouse and your dependents if you do not have a Social Security number
*Proof of foreign status, if applying for an ITIN
*Birth dates for you, your spouse and dependents on the tax return
*Wage and earning statements (Form W-2, W-2G, 1099-R,1099-Misc) from all employers
*Interest and dividend statements from banks (Forms 1099)
*All Forms 1095, Health Insurance Statements
*Health Insurance Exemption Certificate, if received
*A copy of last year federal and state returns, if available
*Proof of bank account routing and account numbers for direct deposit such as a blank check
*To file taxes electronically on a married-filing-joint tax return, both spouses must be present to sign the required forms
*Total paid for daycare provider and the daycare provider's tax identifying number such as their Social Security number or business Employer Identification Number
*Forms 1095-A, B or C, Affordable Health Care Statements
*Copies of income transcripts from IRS, if applicable
name: Volunteer Opportunities

application_process: Complete registration form and registration fee of $25 per camper are submitted and accepted at the UCM/ YEP office. Forms and fees can be mailed in or submitted by hand. Registered campers and parents must attend a one hour orientation session at the camp site on the Saturday (June 4th) before the first day of camp, June 13th. The first weekGs fee will be collected at orientation. Orientation sessions will be scheduled on a first come first registered basis, or at the time the complete registration process is completed.  Intake and registration/ orientation will be on a rolling basis until the camp has reached capacity of 75 campers.

* A resident of Miami-Dade County.
* Must be out-of-school at time of enrollment.
* Must be between 18-24 years old.
* Must be a U.S. Citizen or a Non-Citizen who is in compliance with U. S. Citizenship and Immigration Services.
* Applicant must be low to moderate income individual.
* Applicant must attend an orientation session
* Pass a drug screening (if enrolling in paid work experience component). 
* Complete Miami-Dade County fingerprint requirements.

Eligibility Documents: 

* Florida ID or DriverGs License
* Social Security Card
* Birth Certificate
* Alien Registration Card or other official document Indicating Right to Work
* Proof of Income (Letter of support from parent or guardian with check stub; Public Assistance printout or SSI Letter)

application_process:
Please call to schedule an appointment for a diagnostic assessment. A diagnostic assessment includes both medical and psychological evaluations, a proper diagnosis and critical information about past and present personal, academic and professional life challenges specific to the patient. A diagnostic assessment will provide a picture of the severity of the problem. 

During the call, an intake coordinator will ask for important information including the nature and duration of the addiction, current symptoms, physical and mental health history, problems at home or work and insurance information.

Before arrival for diagnostic assessment, a financial coordinator will help you determine your benefits. On the day of the assessment, please bring a driverGs license and your insurance card.

Once the diagnostic assessment is complete, an addiction specialist will meet with you to explain the results and prescribed recommendations.

The financial coordinator will then work with you and your insurance company to determine coverage and out-of-pocket costs.
name: Comprehensive Outpatient Drug Abuse Treatment

If we both think we can work together we will set up the first meeting to get some history, understand what your immediate and long term concerns are, set some goals to help you feel better while we work on making some more permanent and significant alternations. Every person is different when they come to therapy so every plan varies.
